data.text:
With Sheikh Hasina in India, what happens to her party Awami League in Bangladesh?

timesofindia.com / Aug 12, 2024, 15:37 (IST)

Sheikh Hasina, the former PM of Bangladesh, is in India as Muhammad Yunus-led interim government takes over. The new home minister said her Awami League party will continue, and steps could be taken to bring Hasina back if requested by the law ministry. Her son initially claimed she wouldn't return, but later changed his statement.

Kolkata doctor rape-murder: Stir in govt hospitals across country, docs ask for CBI inquiry

tnn / Aug 13, 2024, 01:24 (IST)

Government hospitals experienced disruptions as resident doctors protested against the rape and murder of a young doctor in Kolkata. The protests, demanding a CBI inquiry and better security, led to suspensions of outpatient services and surgeries in various states. Emergency services, however, continued to operate.

Sheikh Hasina’s ‘prolonged’ stay in India won’t hurt our ties with Delhi: Bangladesh

tnn / Aug 13, 2024, 01:44 (IST)

Bangladesh's ties with India would not be affected under the new interim government, even if former PM Sheikh Hasina remains in India for an extended period. Foreign affairs adviser Md Touhid Hossain assured maintaining good relations. Questions about Hasina's asylum and actions against her by the BNP were raised.

Govt to bring fresh broadcast bill draft after consultations

tnn / Aug 13, 2024, 01:52 (IST)

The information and broadcasting ministry extended the deadline for comments on the draft Broadcasting Services (Regulation) Bill to Oct 15. This follows consultations since last Nov. The proposed legislation aims to overhaul India’s broadcasting regulatory framework but has raised concerns regarding the treatment of independent news creators, initially limited to OTT platforms and digital news, now including social media accounts.

From playschool to trunk breach, how NEET paper leak case was cracked

tnn / Aug 11, 2024, 21:29 (IST)

The NEET-UG exam was held on May 5. Patna police knew the same day that the paper had been leaked and made 13 arrests. But it was not before Lok Sabha polls ended and Centre ordered a CBI probe on June 23 that a clear picture emerged. What went on between May 5 and June-end? A TOI report from Patna

20k-plus job cuts at Dell: Employee says layoffs 'a bit of dumpster fire'

timesofindia.com / Aug 12, 2024, 15:50 (IST)

Earlier this month, Dell announced restructuring efforts focused on AI integration, resulting in workforce reductions. Starting this week, layoffs began across different departments, aiming to reduce the workforce to under 100,000 employees. The restructuring aligns with Dell’s new AI strategy, intending to enhance staff efficiency and streamline solutioning processes, despite concerns about morale and team dynamics.

'Dead for a decade', UP teacher found doing maths at Petrapole

tnn / Aug 13, 2024, 03:03 (IST)

A man found solving mathematical problems on wet soil near the Petrapole border was identified as Amit Kumar Prasad, a missing mathematics teacher from Gorakhpur. Locals alerted police, who then collaborated with Ham radio operators to locate Prasad's family. His father and relatives reunited with him, ending a decade-long search.

Happy Independence Day 2024: Top 50 wishes, messages and quotes

etimes.in / Aug 12, 2024, 23:05 (IST)

Independence Day in India, celebrated on August 15th, marks the significant moment in 1947 when India gained freedom from British rule. This special occasion honors the immense sacrifices made by countless individuals who fought for the nation’s independence. The day is a tribute to their bravery and dedication. To make this occasion even more meaningful and memorable here is a specially curated collection of the top 50 wishes, messages, and inspirational quotes to share with your loved ones.​
